headlines.description: — After getting outhustled and outshot for three quarters, the Los Angeles Clippers turned into a team possessed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard scores 14 points in 5 minutes, Clippers overcome 18-point deficit to stun Nets 125-114

headlines.description: — With its season-opening starting lineup back together for the first time in 2 1/2 months, the Orlando Magic took its defense to another level Sunday night in a 105-87 win over the Miami Heat.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero scores 20 as Magic turn back cold-shooting Heat 105-87

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 42 points, 12 rebounds and eight assists and the defending champion Denver Nuggets beat the Washington Wizards 113-104 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic has 42 points and 12 rebounds, Nuggets beat Wizards 113-104

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis scored 32 points and the NBA-leading Boston Celtics beat the short-handed Houston Rockets 116-107 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kristaps Porzingis scores 32 points, NBA-leading Celtics beat Rockets 116-107

headlines.description: — The Big 3 is starting to become a reality for the Phoenix Suns. Now the wins are beginning to follow.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 40 points, Suns hold off Pacers 117-110 for 5th straight victory

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.shortLinkText: Russell and James dominate 4th quarter in Lakers' 134-110 rout of Trail Blazers
